# Frontend Environment Configuration Examples

## Development (.env.local)

```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
```

This configuration connects the frontend to a local backend API running on port 8080.

## Production (.env.production)

```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
```

In production, the API is typically proxied through the same domain. Adjust the path as needed based on your deployment configuration.

## Notes

- The `VITE_` prefix is required for Vite to inject environment variables into the client
- Make sure the backend API is running before starting the frontend dev server
- CORS must be properly configured on the backend to allow requests from the frontend
